[SN]TITLE[SN]
Billy Caldwell: Santa grotto helps Castlederg boy with epilepsy

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A Castlederg boy who has a severe form of epilepsy has been making huge progress thanks to the support of his local community and a Santa's grotto.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
24 December 2014 Last updated at 13:59 GMT
Billy Caldwell was aged just six months when his mother Charlotte was told by a Royal Belfast Hospital for Sick Children doctor that he would not survive.
BBC Newsline's South West reporter Julian Fowler has the story.
